article.description: — Khalil Shabazz had 22 points, making 4 of 6 3-pointers, and had five steals and San Francisco defeated Santa Clara 73-50 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Shabazz leads San Francisco past Santa Clara 73-50
article.linkText: Shabazz leads San Francisco past Santa Clara 73-50
article.story: SANTA CRUZ, Calif. -- — Khalil Shabazz had 22 points, making 4 of 6 3-pointers, and had five steals and San Francisco defeated Santa Clara 73-50 on Thursday night. Dzmitry Ryuny had 15 points for San Francisco (10-7, 4-3 West Coast Conference). Jamaree Bouyea added 13 points. Josh Kunen had 10 points. Jalen Williams had 15 points and six rebounds for the Broncos (8-4, 2-2). DJ Mitchell added 13 points. Josip Vrankic had 11 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
